    • Constructor Detail

      • Resource

        public Resource(String urlRepresentation)
        Creates Resource instance without the id, that will be part of a REST url
        Parameters:
        urlRepresentation - the string representation of the root resource in the final REST url.
        Note: It is encouraged to have the urlRepresentation as plural values
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if the resource name passed is null or empty

      • Resource

        public Resource(String urlRepresentation,
        String resourceId)
        Creates Resource instance that will be part of a REST url
        Parameters:
        urlRepresentation - the string representation of the root resource in the final REST url.
        Note: It is encouraged to have the urlRepresentation as plural values
        resourceId - the id of the resource in the final REST url
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if a null or empty resource name is passed

    • Method Detail

      • getUrlRepresentation

        public String getUrlRepresentation()

      • getResourceId

        public String getResourceId()
        Returns:
        the resource id of this root Resource instance or NO_RESOURCE_Id if there is no resource id for this root resource

      • getChildResource

        public Resource getChildResource()
        Returns:
        the child Resource of this parent root instance or null if there is no child resource for this root resource

      • setChildResource

        public void setChildResource(Resource childResource)
        Parameters:

      • toString

        public String toString()
        Overrides:
        toString in class Object
        Returns:
        a string url representation of this Resource instance. It returns the url representation along with the resource id till any depth of child Resource that this instance or its child instance has.

        Note : The string representation of the url returned will have the leading '/'
